      "description": "The Global X Intermediate-Term Treasury Ladder ETF (MLDR) is an exchange-traded fund that mostly invests in investment grade fixed income. The fund tracks an index comprised of US Treasury bonds maturing in 3 to 10 years, employing a bond laddering strategy. By rotating investments annually between seven maturity groups, the fund seeks to provide steady yield and manage interest rate risk, focusing on medium-term government bonds MLDR was launched on Sep 9, 2024 and is issued by Global X.",
